This paper deals with the study of graph classes and their structural properties, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT). The focus on chordal graphs, which are a well-studied class of graphs, suggests that cs.CG and cs.GT are likely categories. The paper also involves the study of clique-width, which is a measure of the complexity of graph classes, and is a topic commonly studied in both graph theory and algorithm design (cs.DS, cs.LG).
